org.epochx.gp.op.init
Class FullInitialiser

java.lang.Object
  org.epochx.op.ConfigOperator<GPModel>
      org.epochx.gp.op.init.FullInitialiser
All Implemented Interfaces:
GPInitialiser, ConfigListener, Listener, Initialiser, Operator
public class FullInitialiser
extends ConfigOperator<GPModel>
implements GPInitialiser

Initialisation implementation which produces full program trees down to a specified depth.

If a model is provided then the following parameters are loaded upon every configure event:

  • population size
  • maximum initial program depth
  • syntax
  • program return type
  • random number generator

If the getModel method returns null then no model is set and whatever static parameters have been set as parameters to the constructor or using the standard accessor methods will be used. If any compulsory parameters remain unset when the initialiser is requested to generate new programs, then an IllegalStateException will be thrown.

See Also:
GrowInitialiser, RampedHalfAndHalfInitialiser

getInitialPopulation

public java.util.List<CandidateProgram> getInitialPopulation()
Generates a population of new CandidatePrograms constructed from the Nodes in the syntax attribute. The size of the population will be equal to the population size attribute. All programs in the population are only guarenteed to be unique (as defined by the equals method on GPCandidateProgram) if the isDuplicatesEnabled method returns true. Each program will have a full node tree with a depth equal to the depth attribute.

Specified by:
getInitialPopulation in interface GPInitialiser
Specified by:
getInitialPopulation in interface Initialiser
Returns:
A List of newly generated GPCandidateProgram instances with full node trees.

getInitialProgram

public GPCandidateProgram getInitialProgram()

getFullNodeTree

public Node getFullNodeTree()
Builds a full node tree down to the given depth. As the node tree will be full the maximum and minimum depths of the returned node tree should be equal to the depth argument. The nodes that form the tree will be randomly selected from the nodes provided as the syntax attribute.

Returns:
The root node of a randomly generated full node tree of the requested depth.
